Privacy Policy
Last updated:
February 19, 2025
1. Introduction
Welcome to Mega Photo ("we", "our", or "us"). This Privacy Policy explains how our iOS application ("App") collects, uses, and shares information when you use our App. By using our App, you agree to the collection and use of information in accordance with this Privacy Policy.
2. Information We Collect
Our App uses third-party services that may collect information used to identify you or your device. The primary data collected include:
Device Information:
Information such as device model, operating system version, and unique device identifiers.
Usage Information:
Data about how you interact with the App, including screens viewed, features used, and other diagnostic data.
Crash Data:
When the App crashes, diagnostic data (such as crash logs and device state) is collected to help us diagnose and fix issues.
3. Third-Party Services
We use the following third-party services:
Google AdSense/AdMob:
Our App displays ads through Google’s advertising services. Google may use cookies and device identifiers (such as IDFA on iOS) to serve personalized ads based on your interests. For more information, please review Google’s
Privacy Policy
and
Ad Settings
.
Google Analytics for Firebase:
We use Google Analytics for Firebase to collect usage data and analyze user behavior. This helps us improve the App experience. The data collected is aggregated and anonymized and may include device information, app usage patterns, and geographic data. More details can be found in
Google’s Analytics Privacy Policy
.
Firebase Crashlytics:
To improve app stability and diagnose issues, we use Firebase Crashlytics, which automatically collects crash reports and diagnostic data when errors occur. This information includes crash logs, device information, and app state details. For more information on what Crashlytics collects, please refer to
Google’s Firebase Privacy & Security
.
4. How We Use Your Information
We use the collected data for the following purposes:
To provide and improve our App:
Data from Google Analytics and Crashlytics helps us understand how users interact with our App and identify areas for improvement.
To serve personalized ads:
Google’s advertising services use device identifiers and usage data to deliver ads tailored to your interests.
To diagnose and fix issues:
Crash reports and diagnostic information allow us to identify and resolve technical issues quickly.
5. Data Sharing and Disclosure
We do not sell or rent your personal data. However, third-party service providers (such as Google) may collect and process certain data as described above. They adhere to their own privacy policies and use your data in accordance with applicable law.
6. Your Choices
Opt-Out:
You may opt out of personalized advertising by adjusting your device settings or using the appropriate opt-out links provided by Google.
Limit Data Collection:
Some features of our App may require the collection of data for functionality. Disabling these features (via your device settings) may impact your App experience.
7. Security
We take reasonable measures to protect the information collected by our App. However, no method of transmission over the internet or method of electronic storage is 100% secure. We cannot guarantee absolute security.
8. Changes to This Privacy Policy
We may update our Privacy Policy from time to time. Any changes will be posted on this page with an updated revision date. Your continued use of the App after changes are made will signify your acceptance of the revised policy.
9. Contact Us
If you have any questions or concerns regarding this Privacy Policy, please contact us at:
Falstad.com
apps@falstad.com